{"id":37,"parent_id":34,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":37,"title":"Mark 3: Jesus Attracts Much Attention","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mark 3: Jesus Attracts Much Attention","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-3-jesus-attracts-much-attention","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-3-jesus-attracts-much-attention"},[".heading",{"id":"head4","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-3-jesus-attracts-much-attention.head4"},["h1","Mark 3"],[".subtitle","Jesus Attracts Much Attention"],[".",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-3-jesus-attracts-much-attention.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-041-1.gif"}]],[".intro","We do not know how many people were converted and became members of the Church while Jesus was alive. It seems that the number was quite small, but Mark records that a larger number of people were interested in Jesus—especially when they saw or heard of His miracles.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/3"},"Mark 3"],"is a record of some of the growing interest in Jesus and shows how, as He became more well known, those in positions of power and leadership began to oppose Him and look for ways to disgrace Him in the eyes of the people."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/3"},"Mark 3"]],["p.para",{"id":"p61","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-3-jesus-attracts-much-attention.p61"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/3.1-6"},"Mark 3:1–6"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/12.9-14"},"Matthew 12:9–14"],";",["a.